@alexToken = course-alex-local-token

### Seed the course customer and T-1001; this also clears previous course conversations
POST http://localhost:8080/api/demo/seed

### Turn 1: backend records the sanitized request and action projection
POST http://localhost:8080/api/assistant/orchestrate
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Why is ticket T-1001 unresolved?",
  "conversationId": "course-memory"
}

### Turn 2: send only the new message; backend history supplies the ticket context
POST http://localhost:8080/api/assistant/orchestrate
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Escalate it.",
  "conversationId": "course-memory"
}

### Reopen the panel by loading authorized backend turns; this does not mutate the session
GET http://localhost:8080/api/assistant/conversations/course-memory
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}

### Turn 3: confirmation resolves the owner-scoped pending action exactly once
POST http://localhost:8080/api/assistant/orchestrate
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Yes.",
  "conversationId": "course-memory"
}

### Duplicate approval must not execute the escalation again
POST http://localhost:8080/api/assistant/orchestrate
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Yes.",
  "conversationId": "course-memory"
}

### Intentional isolation proof: this new conversation has no T-1001 context
POST http://localhost:8080/api/assistant/orchestrate
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Escalate it.",
  "conversationId": "course-memory-new"
}

### Deliberate backend reset; closing a browser panel should never call this
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/assistant/conversations/course-memory
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
